§ 3. It ought not to be given to ſuch as are apt to be coſtive, or have hard and dry Bodies, or afflicted with any fly prick Humor, or Scirrhous, or Cancerous Tumors; 
                           •
                        or to Women whoſe Courſes are ſtopt, or are apt to be troubled with Vapors or Hyſterick Fits.

§ 5. Minſicht. pag. 97. makes it of green Vitriol calcin'd to redneſs (which is Colcotha
                              •
                           ) then poudred, and edulcorated by many Ablutions in diſtilled Rain-water, till the Earth be freed from all its Acrimony and ſaltneſs, which he then drys, and keeps for uſe.
